    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nIt is possible to extend the default setting with a file in `{nvim runtime}/lsp/foo.lua`\n\nThis only works for the `settings` key, but not for example with the `filetypes` key.\n\nFor example:\n\n```lua\nreturn {\n    filetypes = { 'bash', 'sh', 'PKGBUILD' }, -- Will be ignored\n    settings = { foo = 'bar' },               -- Will be applied\n};\n```\n\nCurrent workaround:\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config.bashls = {\n    filetypes = { 'bash', 'sh', 'PKGBUILD' },\n};\nreturn {\n    settings = { foo = 'bar' },\n};\n```",
